es Preventing and Resolving Workplace Issues Recruitment and Compensation Research Resources for Faculty Tenure and Promotion UNT Employee Guide UNT Policy Office More UNT Faculty and Staff Resources HomePreventing and Resolving Workplace Issues Ombuds Office — Ombuds actively promotes and supports a fair, respectful, and safe workplace by providing university employees with a confidential, informal, neutral and impartial means of preventing or resolving workplace concerns, problems, or disputes. Office of Institutional Compliance — Institutional Compliance is an independent arm of management with a mission of establishing an Institutional Compliance program that clearly demonstrates UNT System's total commitment to the highest standards of ethics and compliance with all applicable regulatory requirements by its faculty, staff, and students. Division of Institutional Equity and Diversity — The Division of Institutional Equity and Diversity partners with the UNT Faculty and Staff and the entire campus community to create an inclusive environment that prepares and promotes UNT student success in a global marketplace.  At UNT, all members of our community value, support, and respect each other and the educational benefits of diversity. Visit Us   Office of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs370 Hurley Administration Building Mail Us   University of North TexasOffice of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs 1155 Union Circle #311190 Denton, Texas 76203-5017 [map]   Contact Us   940-565-2550 TTY: 940-369-8652 FAX: 940-565-2774 For questions about this website, contact ronda.bewley@unt.edu   Site last updated on: May 09, 2017 Disclaimer  |  AA/EOE/ADA  |  Privacy  |   Electronic Accessibility  |  State of Texas Online  |  Emergency Preparedness  |  THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information  |  UNT Compliance Hotline  |  Governors Committee on People with Disabilities  |  Texas Veterans Portal  |  UNT Home 